check_ssl_cert

A Nagios plugin to check an X.509 certificate:
 - checks if the server is running and delivers a valid certificate
 - checks if the CA matches a given pattern
 - checks the validity


Notes:

the root certificate corresponding to the checked certificate must be available to openssl or specified with the '-r cabundle' option.

On Mac OS X the root certificates bundle is storen in the Keychain and openssl will complain with:

   verification error: unable to get local issuer certificate

The bundle can be extracted with:

$ sudo security find-certificate -a \
  -p /System/Library/Keychains/SystemRootCertificates.keychain > cabundle.crt



